==English==

{{rank|possession|move|foreign|956|native|members|fortune|glass}}

===Etymology===
From Latin [[natus]], birth.

===Adjective===
'''native'''
# belonging to one by [[birth]]; "my native land"; "one's native language"
# characteristic of or relating to people [[inhabiting]] a [[region]] from the [[beginning]]; "native Americans"; "the native peoples of Australia"
# characteristic of or existing by virtue of [[geographic]] [[origin]]; "the native North American sugar maple"; "many native artists studied abroad"
#{{computing}} (''of software'') written specifically to run on a particular processor; "this is a native back-end to gather the latest news feeds"
#{{biology}} (''of a species'') which has [[evolved]] in the given [[locality]], to be contrasted with an invasive species
====Translations====
*Spanish: [[nativo]], [[oriundo]]

===Noun===
'''native'''  (''plural:'' '''[[natives]]''')
# A person who is native to a place (literal or metaphoric)
#:''She is a regular Wiki* '''native'''.''
#:''I need a volunteer '''native''' New Yorker for my next joke...''
# Sometimes used pejoratively against indigenous peoples by their colonizers
#:''Some '''natives''' must have stolen our cattle.''

